olive oil
1 carrot
1 stalk celery
1 leek
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Chicken Drumstick Fillet
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tsp plain flour
¾ cup milk
30 g butter
1 packet filo pastry
½ sachet mixed sesame seeds
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Grate the carrot. Thinly slice celery and white and light green parts of leek. Roughly chop baby spinach leaves.
• Cut boneless chicken drumsticks into 2cm chunks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook chicken and diced bacon, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, then transfer to a baking dish.
• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot, celery and leek stirring, until softened, 4-6 minutes.
• Stir through baby spinach until wilted, 1 minute.

• Add garlic paste, Nan's special seasoning, chicken-style stock powder and the plain flour, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the milk and cook, stirring, until reduced, 2-3 minutes.
• Transfer veggie filling to the baking dish with the chicken and stir to combine.

TIP: Add a splash of water if chicken mixture looks too thick.

• To a small heatproof bowl, add the butter and microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Brush each sheet of filo pastry with butter. Lightly scrunch sheets of pastry and place on top of the chicken mixture to completely cover.
• Sprinkle with sesame seeds (see ingredients).

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the sesame seeds!

• Bake pie until the pastry is golden, 20-25 minutes.

• Divide chicken, bacon and veggie-loaded filo pie between plates. Enjoy!